HAML Notes

> STATIC IDENTIFIERS:
% html    
. class
# id

> DYNAMIC IDENTIFIERS:
= ruby expressions - produces output  
- ruby non printing code - (blocks / variables)
-# (comment)

> STRUCTURE:
Views should only contain view logic (very short directives of ruby code in view code - use helpers instead)
Cooperates - mix and match

> SETUP
gem install haml
install textmate bundles for haml & sass

> SAMPLE - index.haml

!!! Strict
%html
  %head
  %body
    %h1 Hello World

> Run haml index.html  translates it to:

  <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
  <html>
  <head></head>
  <body>
    <h1>Hello World</h1>
  </body>
  </html>